# 🔊 Jarvis - AI-Powered Desktop Voice Assistant

**Jarvis** is an intelligent voice assistant built in Python, capable of performing a wide variety of desktop and internet tasks using voice commands. This assistant can open applications, get weather updates, play YouTube videos, send WhatsApp messages and emails, generate QR codes, translate and transliterate text, play devotional music, check internet speed, and even interact with OpenAI for general queries.

---

## ✨ Features

- 🎙️ Voice-activated command recognition
- 🌐 Real-time weather updates and news
- 📍 Distance & location detection using OpenCage Geocoder
- 🔁 Translate & transliterate text to over 100 languages
- 📚 Wikipedia summary extraction
- 📧 Send Emails and WhatsApp messages
- 📸 Take screenshots and webcam captures
- 💬 Conversational AI (powered by OpenAI)
- 📊 Internet speed checker
- 🔐 Password generation
- 🧠 Rock-Paper-Scissors Game
- 🔔 Reminders and timers
- 📦 Custom application and website launching
- 🔉 Volume control
- 📜 Motivational quotes, jokes, facts, and stories
- 🧘 Meditation & devotional music player

---

## 🛠️ Technologies & Libraries Used

- `Python`
- `SpeechRecognition`, `pyttsx3`, `gTTS`
- `Tkinter`, `Pygame`, `OpenCV`
- `OpenCageGeocode`, `geopy`, `requests`
- `Pytube`, `pycaw`, `schedule`
- `Googletrans`, `deep_translator`
- `Wikipedia`, `TinyDB`, `pywhatkit`
- `OpenAI API`, `Speedtest`, `qrcode`
- `smtplib`, `PIL`, `Indic Transliteration`

---

